d has done fieldwork in Africa, Sri Lanka, the Caribbean, and California.This book is both a memoir and an account of how Dasmann's thinking developed around issues that are vitally important today. In engaging conversational language, he shares his thoughts on issues he has grappled with throughout his life, such as population growth and the question of how sustainability can be measured, understood, and regained. Called by the Wild tells the story of an inspirational risk taker who reminds us that "the earth is the only known nature reserve in the entire universe" and that we must learn to treat it as such.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aConservationistszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  aafrica.  aaustralia.  aautobiography.  abiography.  abiology.  abioregionalism.  abiosphere.  acalifornia.  acaribbean.  aconservation.  adasmann.  aecology.  aecotourism.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental movement.  aenvironmentalism.  afieldwork.  agame management.  akinshasha.  amemoir.  amilitary service.  amilitary.  anatural world.  anature preserve.  anature.  anonfiction.  apolitics.  apopulation growth.  arain forest.  asan francisco.  asoldier.  asouth pacific.  asri lanka.  asustainability.  aunited nations.  aunited states.  aveteran.  awilderness.  awildlife.  aworld war two.  aww2.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092740740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520927407423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520927407/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_Y